7️⃣ AI MONTHLY SUMMARY
Now we design the AI layer properly and cost-efficiently.
Purpose
Generate optimistic, non-threatening, structured summaries:
    • Student-wise
    • Batch-wise
Monthly only.

7.1 Data Source
DO NOT send raw sessions to LLM.
Prepare structured summary object:
{
  "avgRawPercent": 62,
  "avgAccuracyPercent": 71,
  "phaseAdherence": 78,
  "easyNeglectPercent": 22,
  "riskDistribution": {
    "stable": 42,
    "impulsive": 18
  },
  "disciplineIndex": 68,
  "controlledDelta": 12,
  "trendDirection": "improving"
}
Small JSON only.

7.2 Prompt Strategy (Cost Optimized)
Use:
    • Fixed system prompt
    • Structured numeric JSON input
    • Temperature low (0.3)
    • Max tokens capped
Prompt style:
“Generate a constructive academic performance summary using the following metrics. Focus on growth and positive reinforcement. Avoid negative emotional language.”
Keep output under 250 words.

7.3 Generation Schedule
Trigger:
    • End of each month
    • OR manual “Generate Summary” button
Store result in:
aiMonthlySummary/{academicYear}/{entityId}
Never regenerate automatically unless requested.

7.4 Cost Control
    • Generate once per month per batch
    • Generate once per month per student (optional)
    • Cache result
    • Do not regenerate on dashboard load
    • Allow manual refresh only
This keeps LLM usage minimal.

